1 AN ACT relating to motor carrier safety regulation.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 281.600 is amended to read as follows:
4 (1) The Department of Vehicle Regulation shall:
5 (a) Exercise all administrative functions of the state in relation to motor carrier
6 transportation as defined in this chapter;[, and shall ]
7 (b) Apply, as far as practicable, the federal regulations and administrative and
8 judicial interpretations of acts administered by the Federal Motor Carrier
9 Safety Administration and other federal agencies under the United States
10 Department of Transportation;[. It shall ]
11 (c) Have the right to regulate motor carriers as provided in this chapter and[, to
12 that end, may] establish reasonable requirements with respect to continuous
13 and adequate service of transportation, systems of accounts, records and
14 reports, preservation of records, and safety of operation and equipment;
15 (d) Conduct administrative hearings in accordance with KRS Chapter 13B;
16 and[. It may issue subpoenas, subpoenas duces tecum and orders of personal
17 attendance of witnesses, and production of pertinent records for any
18 proceeding before it, and permit the taking of depositions, all in accord with
19 the Rules of Civil Procedure, and it shall have the power to ]
20 (e) Promulgate administrative regulations in accordance with KRS Chapter
21 13A[as it may deem necessary] to carry out the provisions of this chapter,
22 including:
23 1. [. The department shall have the authority to promulgate ]Regulations
24 regarding safety requirements for motor vehicles and the method of
25 operation; and[, including ]
26 2. The adoption of [any of the ]federal motor carrier safety regulations[
27 and ].
