1 (2) Any motor vehicle operating contrary to safety regulations promulgated by the
2 department shall be in violation of this section.
3 (3)[(2)] Notwithstanding any other provision of law to the contrary, the provisions
4 of Title 49 of the United States Code adopted pursuant to subsection (1) of this
5 section, and not otherwise excepted by subsection (4) of this section, shall apply to
6 any driver, vehicle, or motor carrier subject to its jurisdiction within the
7 Commonwealth. Any provision of law that conflicts or is contrary to, or which
8 establishes a different compliance standard than Title 49 of the United States
9 Code adopted pursuant to subsection (1) of this section, and not otherwise
10 excepted by subsection (4) of this section, shall not apply to any driver, vehicle, or
11 motor carrier within the Commonwealth. This subsection shall not be construed
12 to negate any provision of law where Title 49 of the United States Code adopted
13 pursuant to subsection (1) of this section does not apply or where there is no
14 regulatory incompatibility[The provisions established by the Federal Highway
15 Administration in Title 49, Part 393 of the United States Code of Federal
16 Regulations shall not apply to:
17 (a) A motor vehicle or its towed unit having a fertilizer spreader attachment
18 permanently mounted thereon, having a gross weight not to exceed thirty-six
19 thousand (36,000) pounds, and used only for the transportation of bulk
20 fertilizer; or
21 (b) A farm-wagon-type tank trailer of not more than two thousand (2,000) gallon
22 capacity used during liquid fertilizer season as a field storage tank supplying
23 fertilizer to a field applicator, and moved on a public highway for the purpose
24 of bringing fertilizer from a local source of supply to a farm or field, or from
25 one (1) farm or field to another, provided that the vehicle is being operated
26 solely in intrastate transportation.
27 (3) The provisions established by the Federal Highway Administration in 49 C.F.R.
