1 sec. 390.21 and 49 C.F.R. pts. 391, 393, 395, and 396 shall not apply to a motor
2 vehicle registered under KRS 186.050(4)(a)1., or its towed unit, if:
3 (a) The vehicle is not engaged in interstate commerce;
4 (b) The vehicle is engaged in farming or agricultural related activities; and
5 (c) The gross vehicle weight, gross vehicle weight rating, gross vehicle
6 combination weight, or gross vehicle combination weight rating of the vehicle
7 and its towed unit is twenty-six thousand (26,000) pounds or less].
8 (4) The provisions established by the Federal Highway Administration in 49 C.F.R.
9 secs. 391.41 to 391.49 and 49 C.F.R. pt. 395 shall not apply to a motor vehicle
10 registered under KRS 186.050(3)(b) or (4), or its towed unit, if:
11 (a) The vehicle is not engaged in interstate commerce;
12 (b) The vehicle is not transporting hazardous materials required to be placarded in
13 accordance with 49 C.F.R. pt. 172;
14 (c) The vehicle is not designed or used to transport sixteen (16) or more
15 passengers, including the driver; and
16 (d) The gross vehicle weight, gross vehicle weight rating, gross vehicle
17 combination weight, or gross vehicle combination weight rating of the vehicle
18 and its towed unit is twenty-six thousand (26,000) pounds or less.
19 (5) The Department of Kentucky State Police shall exercise all administrative functions
20 of the state pertaining to the motor carrier safety management audit program. This
21 program shall be administered according to the provisions of the Federal Motor
22 Carriers Safety Act and the federal regulations promulgated under that Act.
